column5: The bite that happened just as the sun was setting in the horizon. First fish caught and released about 12 inches then the rest caught within 15 mins and then with a few to take home it was over.  All fish caught on a Green Mister Champ tipped with a minnow. I stopped in and got the minnows at Skevy's and he pointed me in the right direction to find the fish.  Sorry I didn't even have time to take pics on the ice as I was rushing to pack up before dark and didn't want to bother setting up the coleman lantern so I only got this one at home before cleaning them up.
very nice Mister Champ has been a great lure there as long as I can remember
Beauties Mike, well done, you'll never go wrong fishing at sunset !!  See you tomorrow
Well done Mike, like Irish said what time is dinner Hmm fresh walleye! Congrats!  Whopper
WOW!! Great haul and nice lookin eyes you got there.  Hope they are tasty as they look...
Goran's were bigger  LOL just kidding good job man!!!    Try my batter on em, on the recipe page... good eating.   Gerritt.
Nice haul Mike, thinkin shoulda bin there   ...
BEAUTY FISH BRO!! PASS THE BUTTER  LOL
Nice Mike, thanks for posting. Glad you got out.
Thanks everyone.  Lew tomorrow for sure at opening.  Gerritt your recipe is first up and I'll let you know how it goes.  Mike
nice catch smokey...they will be very tasty...and what time did you say dinner was...
Thanks for update and tips. Ice fishing closes there on Feb. 28th. Very nice catch. Gotta love Quinte and the chance at a monster walleye.  Good stuff,  ehg
Nice EYE"S! The night bite can be awesome. Keep hammering those Eye's!
The night time is the right time!
